IMPORTANT guidelines:
- Mark as relevant (confidence >= 0.8) if it contains CONCRETE evidence of malicious behavior: data theft, C2 communication, unauthorized access, covert operations.
- Mark as relevant (confidence 0.5-0.7) if it uses security-sensitive APIs that COULD be abused: network requests (HTTP/sockets), location access, camera/microphone, SMS, file downloads, push notification handling, analytics/tracking, device identifiers. These are worth deeper analysis even if they appear legitimate.
